1
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,240
-Hey!
-Stop!

2
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:35,600
It's me.

3
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:36,920
PREVIOUS EPISODE

4
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:39,800
What about Maria, Joey, and Sophie?

5
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:41,560
They got away,

6
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:44,080
but we've got people chasing them now.

7
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:45,080
Hit them hard!

8
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:46,000
Hurry up!

9
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:55,240
They've got a helicopter.

10
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:57,040
Who are they?

11
00:04:15,640 --> 00:04:16,920
Hey.

12
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:20,279
I'm starting to doubt

13
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:22,600
you're just an ordinary cop.

14
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:26,080
A helicopter showing up like this
for an emergency?

15
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:28,920
Are you hiding something from me?

16
00:04:29,720 --> 00:04:31,280
I've got nothing to hide.

17
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:35,480
I'm just a cop, like Manat.

18
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:38,200
Guess having a heart full of patriotism

19
00:04:38,280 --> 00:04:41,640
is why the country

20
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:43,120
looks out for us.

21
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:52,720
I kinda want to see this goofy Manat

22
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:54,680
sacrifice himself for the country now.

23
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:56,960
It's easy, really.

24
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:59,400
Just marry a cop like me.

25
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:00,920
You'll see it happen every day.

26
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:04,080
-Come on, hurry.
-Too close!

27
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:05,920
Not too close, come on.

28
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,200
-Manat! Hey!
-Come on.

29
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:08,960
-Come here.
-Hey, Manat!

30
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:10,800
-I was joking!
-Yeah.

31
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:15,240
Harder, Maria!

32
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:16,920
More!

33
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:23,840
Hey, why are you poking
your face over here?

34
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:25,600
Waiting for love.

35
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:30,360
Waiting for love, huh?

36
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:33,000
You're a naughty one,
waiting for love, huh?

37
00:05:33,080 --> 00:05:35,520
-Right in the heart.
-Right in the heart?

38
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,800
-So annoying! I really can't help it!
-Hey!

39
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:40,240
Hey! Manat, wait up!

40
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:01,560
I have a bad feeling
something messy's going down there.

41
00:06:02,280 --> 00:06:04,280
Then we'd better hurry back to Khok Ta Yu.

42
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:07,800
Right! I don't know how Dad's doing.

43
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:09,360
I need to call him.

44
00:06:30,520 --> 00:06:31,880
Maria.

45
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:34,360
Where are you?

46
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:37,960
I'm safe, Dad. Someone helped me.
What about you?

47
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,600
They…

48
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:41,960
captured me.

49
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:44,200
What? Did they hurt you?

50
00:06:44,280 --> 00:06:45,320
Get someone

51
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:49,560
to come help me.
I can't hold on much longer.

52
00:06:49,640 --> 00:06:53,960
Dad, send me your location. Can you do it?

53
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:56,000
Yes.

54
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:58,680
I'll send it right now.

55
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:00,440
Okay, got it.

56
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:01,680
What's going on?

57
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:03,240
My dad's been captured.

58
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:08,960
Don't worry. We'll go save him.

59
00:07:23,520 --> 00:07:24,640
Hey!

60
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:29,320
You've been hiding your phone, huh?

61
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:54,680
DARATHONG MUSIC

62
00:07:54,760 --> 00:07:58,560
Mr. Singha, you sent for me.
Is something wrong?

63
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:03,560
The song Chaiya sang on stage last night,

64
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:05,160
you wrote it, right?

65
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:06,840
Yes, that's right.

66
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:08,400
How much to sell it?

67
00:08:10,960 --> 00:08:12,680
I wasn't thinking of selling.

68
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:15,960
Please sell it to me.
I want to perform it.

69
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:19,080
But Chaiya already sang it
on the broadcast.

70
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:23,440
That's just a filler.
He's not a real singer.

71
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:26,000
Please sell it to me.
I want to sing this song.

72
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:27,960
-But…
-Here's the deal.

73
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:30,560
No rush to decide now.

74
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:33,440
But whenever you do decide to sell it,

75
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:35,880
think of me first.

76
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:37,679
I'll pay any price.

77
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:55,080
This is the location.

78
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:57,760
Can you reach your dad right now?

79
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:01,720
No. I don't know how he's doing.

80
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:04,840
Stay calm.

81
00:09:05,520 --> 00:09:07,240
I think Village Head Prueng's inside.

82
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,000
How do you know?

83
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:11,560
Look at the guards.

84
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:13,880
If they're watching like that,

85
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:17,040
someone's definitely inside.

86
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:25,440
Everyone, ready?

87
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:30,920
Manat and I will go in and help him.

88
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:34,160
You have to save my dad.

89
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:37,840
Trust me. You two stay here.

90
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:23,760
Let's go.

91
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:56,280
Village Head. Sir.

92
00:11:00,040 --> 00:11:01,120
Stay quiet.

93
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:04,800
I'm Maria's friend. She's waiting outside.

94
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,160
Let's go.

95
00:11:09,160 --> 00:11:10,160
I've got you.

96
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:14,960
Can you manage?

97
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:17,560
Let's go.

98
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:28,400
Dad!

99
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:32,920
Maria, my dear.

100
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:36,840
Quick. We need to get out of here.

101
00:11:36,920 --> 00:11:39,720
Manat, you take him that way.

102
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:42,200
Captain, Miss Puna, and I
will go this way

103
00:11:42,280 --> 00:11:43,520
to draw them away.

104
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:45,640
Wow, very professional.

105
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:48,560
It's standard hostage rescue tactics.
Let's move.

106
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:50,520
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

107
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:51,680
Take it slow. Careful.

108
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:01,080
What's going on?

109
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:06,920
He got away, Chit.
Someone came to help him.

110
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:09,560
Damn it!

111
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:12,000
Village Head Prueng.

112
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:26,680
I haven't been able to reach anyone.

113
00:12:26,760 --> 00:12:28,200
The batteries might be dead.

114
00:12:28,280 --> 00:12:29,560
What about Chaiya?

115
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:31,680
I haven't reached him yet.

116
00:12:33,280 --> 00:12:34,360
No need.

117
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,080
I'll call him myself.

118
00:12:58,320 --> 00:12:59,240
Sorry, Puna.

119
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:01,280
I can't take you myself.

120
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:03,040
Au will take you instead.

121
00:13:03,640 --> 00:13:05,960
It's fine. Go back to the company.
I understand.

122
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:09,280
Puna.

123
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:13,360
Where did you go with Chaiya?

124
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:14,960
Is there a problem?

125
00:13:15,040 --> 00:13:16,760
You can't do this.

126
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:19,560
You can't go off with Chaiya alone.

127
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:23,080
You have no right to stop me, Mr. Sonrak.

128
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:25,160
I love you, Puna.

129
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:27,240
If I've ever done anything wrong,
I'm sorry.

130
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:29,320
But don't do this, Puna.

131
00:13:29,400 --> 00:13:30,360
I love you.

132
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:31,400
Au.

133
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:34,240
Please take me to Bai Tong Music.

134
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:35,240
Yes.

135
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:36,320
I'm off.

136
00:13:38,640 --> 00:13:41,040
Puna.

137
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:00,440
Chaiya.

138
00:14:02,360 --> 00:14:03,400
Because of you.

139
00:14:04,640 --> 00:14:05,600
Because of you!

140
00:14:07,120 --> 00:14:10,160
You're a torment! You're a real obstacle!
I'll kill you!

141
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:16,560
Who'd accept this? Why are you doing it?

142
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:19,400
-Stop! Separate them, now!
-No way! I'll kill you!

143
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:23,440
Let go! Let go!

144
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:26,320
-Let go of me!
-Hey!

145
00:14:27,680 --> 00:14:28,840
Let go!

146
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:38,240
Well.

147
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:41,760
Sonrak loves Puna. You know that, right?

148
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:44,600
Yes, sir.

149
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:47,080
And you disappeared with Puna all night.

150
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:49,280
Of course he'd be angry.

151
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:52,800
This little thing
isn't worth holding a grudge over.

152
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:56,440
But I didn't do anything to him.

153
00:14:58,920 --> 00:15:00,480
Then where were you both all night?

154
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:03,200
Ever since the live broadcast,

155
00:15:04,040 --> 00:15:05,880
the media's been calling non-stop.

156
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:07,880
Also, a YouTube channel

157
00:15:08,560 --> 00:15:11,440
asked Puna and me to do an interview.

158
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:21,120
Now that you're so famous,

159
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:24,800
do you still want to work with me?

160
00:15:26,440 --> 00:15:27,360
Of course.

161
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:29,160
I don't want to be a singer.

162
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:31,720
I still want to work with you.

163
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:39,480
Then help convince Teacher Mueangphrai

164
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:42,240
to sell me the song, "My Request".

165
00:15:47,760 --> 00:15:49,120
"My Request"?

166
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:01,160
-Take it slow.
-Can I get you something?

167
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:03,320
Oh!

168
00:16:05,320 --> 00:16:06,400
Mom.

169
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:11,120
Something happened.
Can Dad and I stay here for now?

170
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:13,960
Sure, come in.

171
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:26,800
What happened to you?

172
00:16:28,640 --> 00:16:30,160
I'll explain everything soon, Mom.

173
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:32,680
Are you disgusted?

174
00:16:32,760 --> 00:16:35,120
Hey, still mouthy, old man?

175
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:37,000
Don't make me scold you.

176
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:39,840
Dad, Mom, can you not argue right now?

177
00:16:39,920 --> 00:16:41,720
Let's work together first.

178
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:45,400
I'm fine.

179
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:47,360
But the way your mom's looking at me,

180
00:16:48,640 --> 00:16:50,040
it makes me uneasy.

181
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:51,640
Hey, old man!

182
00:16:52,280 --> 00:16:53,320
Are you staying here or not?

183
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:55,720
Behave yourself, or I'll scold you!

184
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:56,800
Right now,

185
00:16:57,560 --> 00:16:59,480
we're guests here.

186
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:01,560
We have to behave, dear.

187
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:06,520
Then I'll take my leave.

188
00:17:06,599 --> 00:17:07,520
Oh.

189
00:17:07,599 --> 00:17:09,319
Thank you so much for helping.

190
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:12,920
If you need to go outside,
better cover your face.

191
00:17:13,960 --> 00:17:15,119
Got it.

192
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:18,480
Thanks a lot for helping, young man.

193
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:21,680
My pleasure. If you need anything,
just contact me.

194
00:17:23,079 --> 00:17:24,280
I'll head off now.

195
00:17:24,839 --> 00:17:26,599
Goodbye.

196
00:17:30,560 --> 00:17:32,200
Can we trust this guy?

197
00:17:32,280 --> 00:17:34,640
He said he's a cop.

198
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:38,400
He knows what happened last night
and is figuring out how to help us.

199
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:42,720
That's good.

200
00:17:52,440 --> 00:17:55,240
You're really going to sell
the song to Mr. Singha?

201
00:17:55,320 --> 00:17:56,280
Yes.

202
00:17:57,240 --> 00:17:59,200
But I already turned him down once.

203
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:01,400
This song's about to be a hit.

204
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:04,040
He'll do whatever it takes, Teacher.

205
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:08,640
How about this?

206
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:11,960
Tell him I'm free tomorrow

207
00:18:12,040 --> 00:18:13,720
to sign the contract at his place,

208
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:15,160
and Puna will come too.

209
00:18:17,720 --> 00:18:20,360
So you agree with me, Teacher?

210
00:18:20,440 --> 00:18:21,400
Yes.

211
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:23,960
It's just one song. I can trade it.

212
00:18:25,520 --> 00:18:26,960
Trade it for what?

213
00:18:28,560 --> 00:18:29,960
That teddy bear.

214
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:48,920
Puna.

215
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:51,080
Hello.

216
00:18:52,720 --> 00:18:53,840
-Hello, Teacher.
-Hello.

217
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:57,920
Puna, I'm really glad

218
00:18:58,520 --> 00:19:00,200
that you came,

219
00:19:00,760 --> 00:19:02,280
no matter the reason.

220
00:19:05,440 --> 00:19:08,280
Please, have a seat.
Teacher, please have a seat.

221
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:20,080
Teacher, thank you
for agreeing to sell me the song.

222
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:23,040
I really appreciate your kindness.

223
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:26,080
I thought it over.

224
00:19:26,920 --> 00:19:30,560
If this song stayed with Darathong Music,
it'd probably be bigger than elsewhere.

225
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:33,640
Chaiya called me,

226
00:19:33,720 --> 00:19:35,120
so I agreed.

227
00:19:37,720 --> 00:19:40,760
I'm here with the teacher.
I hope that's okay.

228
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:42,880
Why would it be a problem?

229
00:19:43,880 --> 00:19:45,120
That's even better.

230
00:19:50,280 --> 00:19:52,560
I've prepared the contract. Take a look.

231
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:18,320
If you sell me the song,

232
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:23,120
I'll promote it fully.
I promise this song will be a hit.

233
00:20:25,080 --> 00:20:27,200
I think if I get to sing this song,

234
00:20:27,880 --> 00:20:29,360
it's going to be huge.

235
00:20:34,040 --> 00:20:35,360
Before we sign the contract,

236
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:39,520
I want to read it first.

237
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:41,960
We need to be careful.

238
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:44,600
Sure, take your time.

239
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:33,160
Well, I read a bit slowly.

240
00:21:33,240 --> 00:21:35,480
My eyesight isn't very good.

241
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:37,640
That's fine.

242
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:48,640
Dad, my phone's dead.

243
00:21:48,720 --> 00:21:51,200
The battery must be weak.
I'll go grab the charger.

244
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:22,280
Where's the charger?

245
00:22:31,680 --> 00:22:32,680
Oh.

246
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:56,080
The teddy bear.

247
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:01,200
Where did Mom's teddy bear go?

248
00:23:05,080 --> 00:23:07,920
Aunt Riam!

249
00:23:13,840 --> 00:23:15,720
DONE

250
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:29,600
I've read it. No problems.

251
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:34,400
Then please sign here.

252
00:23:35,160 --> 00:23:38,120
I promise I'll take
the best care of your song.

253
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:39,760
Alright.

254
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:43,200
I entrust this song to you.

255
00:23:43,280 --> 00:23:45,160
Every song I've written,

256
00:23:45,240 --> 00:23:46,560
I love it like my own child.

257
00:23:47,280 --> 00:23:49,480
I want it to succeed.

258
00:23:50,960 --> 00:23:53,440
Don't worry, Teacher. I promise

259
00:23:53,520 --> 00:23:55,840
I'll promote it to be a hit.

260
00:23:55,920 --> 00:23:57,960
It'll be bigger than it was with you.

261
00:24:11,040 --> 00:24:13,800
If everything's done,
let's go back, Teacher.

262
00:24:13,880 --> 00:24:16,000
Alright, we'll head back now.

263
00:24:16,760 --> 00:24:17,840
Sure, no problem.

264
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:20,440
Aunt Riam!

265
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:21,760
Where are you, Aunt Riam?

266
00:24:23,040 --> 00:24:24,280
Aunt Riam!

267
00:24:28,760 --> 00:24:29,840
Aunt Riam!

268
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:33,480
Aunt Riam! Where are you, Aunt Riam?

269
00:24:34,880 --> 00:24:36,320
Aunt Riam!

270
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:38,080
Yes, Mr. Sonrak?

271
00:24:38,160 --> 00:24:39,560
What do you want?

272
00:24:39,640 --> 00:24:41,280
Where's my teddy bear?

273
00:24:43,400 --> 00:24:45,600
Your teddy bear? I don't know.

274
00:24:45,680 --> 00:24:47,960
I haven't even been in your room today.

275
00:24:48,040 --> 00:24:50,720
If you didn't go in, then who did?
My bear's gone!

276
00:24:50,800 --> 00:24:52,000
I really don't know.

277
00:24:52,080 --> 00:24:54,600
How can you not know? It's not there!

278
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:56,000
Who else would go in but you?

279
00:24:56,080 --> 00:24:57,240
What's going on?

280
00:24:58,040 --> 00:25:00,080
Hey, you're loud enough
to hear from all the way over here.

281
00:25:00,840 --> 00:25:03,960
Dad, someone stole my stuff from my room.

282
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:07,040
What's missing?

283
00:25:08,360 --> 00:25:09,680
Mom's teddy bear.

284
00:25:11,160 --> 00:25:12,440
Your mom's teddy bear?

285
00:25:13,240 --> 00:25:14,400
What would anyone do with that?

286
00:25:14,480 --> 00:25:17,800
Well, a little while ago,

287
00:25:17,880 --> 00:25:20,280
I saw Mr. Chaiya hanging around our house,

288
00:25:20,360 --> 00:25:22,240
acting suspicious.

289
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:25,360
I was about to ask why he was here,
then he was gone.

290
00:25:27,280 --> 00:25:28,480
It's Chaiya, Dad.

291
00:25:29,560 --> 00:25:31,000
He's the thief.

292
00:25:33,240 --> 00:25:34,560
Wait! Don't go yet.

293
00:25:39,280 --> 00:25:40,520
Chaiya came with you, right?

294
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:44,360
No, just the two of us.

295
00:25:45,280 --> 00:25:46,480
It has to be Chaiya, Dad!

296
00:25:48,760 --> 00:25:50,160
If it's not him, then who else?

297
00:25:54,040 --> 00:25:55,080
Chaiya.

298
00:26:02,920 --> 00:26:04,240
Chaiya.

299
00:26:05,520 --> 00:26:06,560
You petty thief!

300
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:10,160
Why are you hitting me?

301
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:11,440
Why did you steal my bear?

302
00:26:12,040 --> 00:26:14,120
-Why did you take it?
-I didn't!

303
00:26:14,200 --> 00:26:15,240
What's going on?

304
00:26:15,320 --> 00:26:17,040
He stole my bear!

305
00:26:19,520 --> 00:26:22,640
I found this teddy bear
in the middle of the yard,

306
00:26:22,720 --> 00:26:25,040
so I picked it up to return it.

307
00:26:25,120 --> 00:26:27,440
It's in your hands. You're lying again!

308
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:28,760
Hey, stop!

309
00:26:30,160 --> 00:26:32,960
Puna, why are you stopping me?
He's a thief!

310
00:26:33,040 --> 00:26:35,640
How can you be so sure Chaiya stole it?

311
00:26:36,560 --> 00:26:37,800
If he did,

312
00:26:37,880 --> 00:26:41,040
he could've taken something
far more valuable than this bear.

313
00:26:42,520 --> 00:26:45,600
Right! If he really stole it,
he'd be long gone.

314
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:50,880
But here he is, coming back.

315
00:26:53,160 --> 00:26:55,040
Then how did it disappear from my room?

316
00:26:56,800 --> 00:26:59,640
Aunt Riam probably took it out to air
and forgot,

317
00:26:59,720 --> 00:27:01,560
so it fell, just like last time.

318
00:27:02,320 --> 00:27:03,640
That's right.

319
00:27:03,720 --> 00:27:04,880
Last time too.

320
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:08,400
You were probably busy and didn't notice

321
00:27:09,280 --> 00:27:11,840
that it was left out in the sun.

322
00:27:27,680 --> 00:27:29,960
If I hadn't caught him red-handed,

323
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:35,040
I'd think it was you, Puna.

324
00:27:37,040 --> 00:27:37,880
Why?

325
00:27:38,640 --> 00:27:40,600
How many times

326
00:27:40,680 --> 00:27:42,440
has this bear been involved with you now?

327
00:27:42,520 --> 00:27:44,280
Mr. Singha, don't say that.

328
00:27:44,360 --> 00:27:46,000
If she didn't do it,

329
00:27:46,080 --> 00:27:47,640
it'll just discourage her.

330
00:27:49,360 --> 00:27:53,120
Dad, it's not Puna.
It's Chaiya who took it!

331
00:27:54,400 --> 00:27:55,760
Alright.

332
00:27:58,480 --> 00:27:59,680
So why are you here?

333
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:03,440
I came to tell you

334
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:06,880
that Teacher Mueangphrai
has decided to sell

335
00:28:07,440 --> 00:28:10,480
the song "My Request", like you asked.

336
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:13,400
But I didn't expect him to come first.

337
00:28:14,840 --> 00:28:16,080
I already know about that.

338
00:28:19,680 --> 00:28:23,600
If that's all, go back inside.
Don't make a scene in front of the house.

339
00:28:44,680 --> 00:28:47,360
Then I'll take my leave.

340
00:28:48,960 --> 00:28:50,160
Goodbye.

341
00:28:57,400 --> 00:28:58,480
I really didn't steal it.

342
00:29:01,960 --> 00:29:03,240
Go wherever you want.

343
00:29:15,840 --> 00:29:19,480
Again, we finally got the bear,

344
00:29:19,560 --> 00:29:21,400
and they took it back.

345
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:24,240
Calm down, Puna.
There'll be another chance.

346
00:29:24,880 --> 00:29:26,800
How many more times
do I have to wait, Teacher?

347
00:29:34,360 --> 00:29:35,560
Chaiya.

348
00:29:36,240 --> 00:29:38,640
Why didn't you run off with the bear?

349
00:29:38,720 --> 00:29:40,560
You just stood there
until they took it back.

350
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:45,920
Yeah, I really want to know
why you did that.

351
00:29:47,520 --> 00:29:50,080
They got the teddy bear, but…

352
00:29:51,280 --> 00:29:52,280
we got the tape.

353
00:29:54,160 --> 00:29:55,960
Where's the tape?

354
00:30:03,560 --> 00:30:04,840
Where did he go?

355
00:30:11,160 --> 00:30:12,080
Here for the package.

356
00:30:13,120 --> 00:30:14,400
Why are you so late?

357
00:30:14,480 --> 00:30:15,880
Curious? It's a long story.

358
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:17,320
Don't bother explaining.

359
00:30:24,040 --> 00:30:24,880
Just go.

360
00:30:26,400 --> 00:30:27,360
Yeah.

361
00:30:38,240 --> 00:30:41,160
So, the tape's with Manat?

362
00:30:41,880 --> 00:30:42,720
Yes.

363
00:30:44,080 --> 00:30:47,440
Good thing you were careful
and called Manat to get the tape.

364
00:30:47,520 --> 00:30:49,680
Otherwise, they'd have taken
the bear back.

365
00:30:50,680 --> 00:30:54,240
I returned the bear because I was worried
they'd get suspicious.

366
00:30:54,800 --> 00:30:57,760
I was going to toss it over there,
but Sonrak saw it first.

367
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:01,760
Thank you so much, Chaiya.

368
00:31:01,840 --> 00:31:03,560
Without you,

369
00:31:03,640 --> 00:31:06,680
I couldn't have gotten
that evidence out myself.

370
00:31:07,720 --> 00:31:09,640
You're amazing. Well done, Captain!

371
00:31:10,480 --> 00:31:11,600
Of course.

372
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:17,360
Wait, what did you just say, Puna?

373
00:31:22,920 --> 00:31:26,720
Sorry, Teacher.
I forgot to tell you earlier.

374
00:31:29,480 --> 00:31:33,040
Don't tell me Chaiya is…

375
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:35,120
Yes.

376
00:31:36,040 --> 00:31:39,280
Actually, this was
my responsibility all along.

377
00:31:39,360 --> 00:31:41,280
Your responsibility as a cop

378
00:31:42,080 --> 00:31:46,200
or as a boyfriend? Be clear!

379
00:31:59,440 --> 00:32:03,040
Dad, are you okay? Walk slowly.

380
00:32:03,120 --> 00:32:04,560
It hurts, dear.

381
00:32:16,320 --> 00:32:17,560
Dad!

382
00:32:19,120 --> 00:32:20,240
Hey!

383
00:32:20,320 --> 00:32:21,160
Who's that?

384
00:32:21,240 --> 00:32:23,280
-Dad, slowly.
-Uncle!

385
00:32:24,840 --> 00:32:26,680
-Get up slowly.
-Let me help.

386
00:32:26,760 --> 00:32:28,760
Sorry. Are you hurt?

387
00:32:29,600 --> 00:32:32,000
How were you driving?
No sound, no warning.

388
00:32:35,560 --> 00:32:36,560
Done at the doctor?

389
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:37,600
Yes.

390
00:32:38,720 --> 00:32:40,440
This way, I'll take you back.

391
00:32:41,320 --> 00:32:43,200
-Let's go, Dad.
-Take it slow.

392
00:33:22,440 --> 00:33:24,560
SCREEN PROTECTOR, FROM 100 BAHT
QUICK REPAIRS

393
00:33:24,640 --> 00:33:25,880
Take it slow, Dad.

394
00:33:29,280 --> 00:33:30,480
Ugh.

395
00:33:32,520 --> 00:33:34,040
Alright.

396
00:33:34,120 --> 00:33:36,680
Oh, you're here, dear?

397
00:33:36,760 --> 00:33:37,840
Yes, Mom.

398
00:33:38,440 --> 00:33:40,880
What have you been up to lately?

399
00:33:40,960 --> 00:33:42,760
Always getting into trouble.

400
00:33:42,840 --> 00:33:45,320
If you don't know, just stay quiet.

401
00:33:45,400 --> 00:33:47,400
Hey, this is my house!

402
00:33:47,480 --> 00:33:49,840
I can say whatever I want.
If it bothers you, go home!

403
00:33:51,680 --> 00:33:55,440
Come on, Mom. He just fell.
He didn't do anything wrong.

404
00:33:56,120 --> 00:33:59,840
I'm sorry. I startled him,
and that's why he fell.

405
00:34:01,760 --> 00:34:04,680
Next time, make him fall harder!

406
00:34:04,760 --> 00:34:06,280
Really knock him down!

407
00:34:06,360 --> 00:34:07,320
Your mouth

408
00:34:07,880 --> 00:34:09,320
never changes.

409
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:10,880
What was that?

410
00:34:11,480 --> 00:34:14,760
Well, you still love her.

411
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:17,239
How do you know I love her?

412
00:34:18,040 --> 00:34:19,239
A wife like this,

413
00:34:19,800 --> 00:34:21,520
I drew the short straw.

414
00:34:27,400 --> 00:34:30,760
I'm sorry for causing you
to get hurt, Village Head.

415
00:34:30,840 --> 00:34:32,719
It's not your fault.

416
00:34:32,800 --> 00:34:34,920
It's my fault.

417
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:37,520
I came back beaten,

418
00:34:37,600 --> 00:34:40,199
seeking help from someone so heartless.

419
00:34:40,280 --> 00:34:41,320
Look at me.

420
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:44,440
All bruised, and she still doesn't care.

421
00:34:44,520 --> 00:34:47,239
All she does is nag me! Geez!

422
00:34:47,320 --> 00:34:48,239
Next time,

423
00:34:48,320 --> 00:34:51,719
if you hit him, go all out!

424
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:54,520
I'm tired of listening
to all this nagging.

425
00:34:56,159 --> 00:34:57,280
Hey, Manat.

426
00:34:58,160 --> 00:34:59,440
Thank you so much.

427
00:35:00,080 --> 00:35:03,560
Last time, if you hadn't helped,

428
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:08,360
my daughter and I might've been dead.

429
00:35:09,240 --> 00:35:12,840
Yes, Village Head. But from now on,
please don't leave the house.

430
00:35:13,600 --> 00:35:15,920
If they spot you,
it'll be trouble for sure.

431
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:17,240
Don't worry.

432
00:35:17,320 --> 00:35:19,080
I'll chain him up

433
00:35:19,160 --> 00:35:21,080
and put a muzzle on him.

434
00:35:21,160 --> 00:35:25,480
He can only stay in the house.
Bark all he wants, he can't go anywhere.

435
00:35:25,560 --> 00:35:29,160
Hey, I'm your ex-husband, not a dog!

436
00:35:30,880 --> 00:35:32,800
I'm starting to believe it.

437
00:35:32,880 --> 00:35:34,640
People say

438
00:35:35,680 --> 00:35:39,680
a good husband is the new one.

439
00:35:46,640 --> 00:35:50,320
Alright, I'll take my leave,
so you can rest.

440
00:35:51,320 --> 00:35:52,720
I'll go with you.

441
00:36:01,400 --> 00:36:02,480
Does it hurt?

442
00:36:09,720 --> 00:36:10,720
Manat.

443
00:36:11,960 --> 00:36:14,400
Ever since what happened,
Dad and I haven't slept.

444
00:36:16,960 --> 00:36:19,400
Do you think this place is safe enough?

445
00:36:21,040 --> 00:36:22,360
It's safe for now.

446
00:36:23,200 --> 00:36:26,520
But I'll find a new place
for you to hide soon.

447
00:36:31,320 --> 00:36:32,840
Thank you.

448
00:36:33,520 --> 00:36:35,080
If you need anything,

449
00:36:35,840 --> 00:36:37,040
just tell me.

450
00:36:38,440 --> 00:36:41,560
I'll come to you as soon as you need me.

451
00:37:34,160 --> 00:37:35,480
Mom, where's Dad?

452
00:37:36,760 --> 00:37:38,160
Inside, dear.

453
00:37:43,040 --> 00:37:46,520
Honestly, I don't want
you and Dad to fight.

454
00:37:48,920 --> 00:37:50,560
I'll be honest too.

455
00:37:51,200 --> 00:37:52,600
Every time I see your dad,

456
00:37:52,680 --> 00:37:54,640
I get annoyed.

457
00:37:54,720 --> 00:37:55,760
Can't help myself!

458
00:37:57,480 --> 00:37:59,480
You're just like that.

459
00:38:13,080 --> 00:38:14,560
Is this yours, Mom?

460
00:38:23,280 --> 00:38:25,120
I haven't seen a tape like this in ages.

461
00:38:25,200 --> 00:38:27,280
Nobody uses these anymore.

462
00:38:29,560 --> 00:38:31,040
Where did you get it?

463
00:38:32,240 --> 00:38:33,880
Then it must be Manat's.

464
00:38:35,400 --> 00:38:36,680
I'll try calling him.

465
00:38:42,280 --> 00:38:43,320
Wait.

466
00:38:45,400 --> 00:38:47,880
Something's wrong with my phone.
The screen won't turn on.

467
00:38:50,040 --> 00:38:50,880
Let me see.

468
00:38:51,480 --> 00:38:54,520
Did you drop it?

469
00:38:55,480 --> 00:38:59,040
Want to use my phone to call?
Here, take it.

470
00:38:59,120 --> 00:39:01,120
-I'll check this for you.
-Well.

471
00:39:02,080 --> 00:39:04,360
I can't remember his number.

472
00:39:04,440 --> 00:39:06,080
It's saved in my phone.

473
00:39:08,120 --> 00:39:10,240
-I'll fix it for you.
-Okay.

474
00:39:11,920 --> 00:39:14,760
Wow, you're amazing!

475
00:39:14,840 --> 00:39:16,360
You can even fix a phone.

476
00:39:18,320 --> 00:39:20,120
Well, I didn't want to sell coffee!

477
00:39:28,680 --> 00:39:29,800
What's up?

478
00:39:29,880 --> 00:39:30,760
Chit.

479
00:39:31,360 --> 00:39:35,120
I found Village Head Prueng
and his daughter.

480
00:39:50,120 --> 00:39:51,640
-Teacher.
-Oops!

481
00:40:06,560 --> 00:40:08,400
Very sweet, indeed.

482
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:11,240
Wow.

483
00:40:22,120 --> 00:40:23,800
Who did Chaiya bring with him?

484
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:25,160
Let's go inside.

485
00:40:33,880 --> 00:40:35,200
He's letting her go into the room.

486
00:40:37,520 --> 00:40:38,480
Nammon.

487
00:40:39,080 --> 00:40:42,000
Nammon, calm down.

488
00:40:42,080 --> 00:40:43,760
We’re fellow Thais.

489
00:40:44,680 --> 00:40:46,000
That means no mercy for her!

490
00:40:47,560 --> 00:40:49,160
-When it comes to looks,
-Yeah.

491
00:40:49,920 --> 00:40:51,760
-don't get me started.
-Then don't say a word.

492
00:40:52,800 --> 00:40:53,640
Can't I say something?

493
00:40:53,720 --> 00:40:55,320
Okay, if I have to say it,

494
00:40:55,400 --> 00:40:57,520
Auntie, your outfit is good all over,

495
00:40:57,600 --> 00:40:59,280
but one thing isn't.

496
00:40:59,360 --> 00:41:00,320
Your shoes.

497
00:41:02,600 --> 00:41:04,160
Can't you find a better pair?

498
00:41:04,240 --> 00:41:05,640
-Here they are.
-What?

499
00:41:05,720 --> 00:41:08,040
Why are you carrying it? Why not wear it?

500
00:41:08,120 --> 00:41:10,280
I'm in a hurry, and my leg hurts.

501
00:41:10,360 --> 00:41:11,880
Whoa.

502
00:41:11,960 --> 00:41:15,000
If you're not wearing it, why not leave it
in your room? Why carry it?

503
00:41:15,080 --> 00:41:16,360
So people know I've got it.

504
00:41:16,440 --> 00:41:18,480
Talking nonsense again.
What a crazy person!

505
00:41:18,560 --> 00:41:21,000
What’s so beautiful about her?

506
00:41:21,080 --> 00:41:21,960
Everything.

507
00:41:23,720 --> 00:41:24,720
That brat!

508
00:41:24,800 --> 00:41:25,680
Her?

509
00:41:25,760 --> 00:41:28,000
-No, you!
-Hold on!

510
00:41:28,080 --> 00:41:29,120
-Just once!
-Auntie!

511
00:41:29,200 --> 00:41:31,960
-Can't take it anymore.
-Auntie!

512
00:41:32,040 --> 00:41:34,920
-Don't, Auntie!
-What's your problem?

513
00:41:37,080 --> 00:41:38,680
Make yourself comfortable.

514
00:41:38,760 --> 00:41:41,640
I'll call Manat to see where he is.

515
00:42:01,440 --> 00:42:03,280
Can't reach him?

516
00:42:03,360 --> 00:42:06,720
He's not answering. Probably driving.

517
00:42:06,800 --> 00:42:09,440
Never mind. He's probably on his way.

518
00:42:11,840 --> 00:42:14,600
Teacher, then I'll call Aunt Wilai

519
00:42:14,680 --> 00:42:15,720
to tell her we got the tape.

520
00:42:16,840 --> 00:42:18,800
She'll be so happy.

521
00:42:18,880 --> 00:42:19,960
Yes.

522
00:42:29,560 --> 00:42:32,920
Aunt Wilai, we have the evidence tape now.

523
00:42:34,880 --> 00:42:37,680
Yes, it's with someone else at the moment,

524
00:42:37,760 --> 00:42:39,400
but as soon as I get it,

525
00:42:39,480 --> 00:42:41,600
I'll bring it to you immediately.

526
00:42:43,280 --> 00:42:45,920
Okay, that's all for now.

527
00:42:46,520 --> 00:42:47,760
See you.

528
00:42:57,160 --> 00:43:00,400
So this is Puna,
the girl who sang "Soft Heart"?

529
00:43:04,120 --> 00:43:05,280
Looking at you,

530
00:43:05,360 --> 00:43:07,360
you can't compare to me,

531
00:43:07,440 --> 00:43:09,440
totally worlds apart.

532
00:43:09,520 --> 00:43:11,720
That's right, Auntie.

533
00:43:11,800 --> 00:43:14,040
The gold necklace, wear it, pile it on!

534
00:43:14,120 --> 00:43:15,720
It's as chunky as a pinky.

535
00:43:15,800 --> 00:43:20,360
A red top with a blue skirt? Really?
What a mismatch!

536
00:43:20,440 --> 00:43:21,520
You're roasting her, right?

537
00:43:21,600 --> 00:43:24,000
-Roast her, of course!
-Perfect.

538
00:43:24,080 --> 00:43:25,600
Full support here!

539
00:43:25,680 --> 00:43:27,120
Exactly, Auntie!

540
00:43:28,040 --> 00:43:29,160
What kind of girl

541
00:43:29,240 --> 00:43:32,240
comes to a guy's house like this?

542
00:43:32,320 --> 00:43:34,280
Aren't you afraid

543
00:43:34,360 --> 00:43:36,800
people will say you're wild?

544
00:43:38,480 --> 00:43:41,280
Hey, but you guys are here too.

545
00:43:42,120 --> 00:43:43,920
Whoa! My goodness!

546
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:45,880
That's harsh. Nammon!

547
00:43:45,960 --> 00:43:49,560
She's basically saying
you're just as wild.

548
00:43:49,640 --> 00:43:51,600
That's why you're at a guy's house too.

549
00:43:51,680 --> 00:43:53,640
-Harsh! Okay.
-Not the same!

550
00:43:54,680 --> 00:43:56,640
-I'm his ex.
-Yeah.

551
00:43:57,680 --> 00:44:01,000
I can come and go as I please.

552
00:44:01,080 --> 00:44:02,320
But you…

553
00:44:03,520 --> 00:44:06,560
Who are you? Can't be here.

554
00:44:07,080 --> 00:44:08,280
Yeah.

555
00:44:09,040 --> 00:44:11,560
I'm Dada, by the way.

556
00:44:11,640 --> 00:44:14,080
A friend of his ex.

557
00:44:14,160 --> 00:44:15,160
But you…

558
00:44:15,720 --> 00:44:17,800
Who are you?

559
00:44:17,880 --> 00:44:19,400
Better tell us quickly.

560
00:44:20,400 --> 00:44:21,560
Well, not an ex.

561
00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:25,680
Oh wow, she's serving it again!

562
00:44:25,760 --> 00:44:27,160
She means

563
00:44:27,240 --> 00:44:30,280
you're just an ex, like spoiled curry,

564
00:44:30,360 --> 00:44:35,440
-old chili paste, secondhand shoes, used--
-Shut up!

565
00:44:35,520 --> 00:44:37,240
You really talk too much.

566
00:44:39,800 --> 00:44:41,880
So here you are.

567
00:44:41,960 --> 00:44:44,280
-The hidden beauty gang!
-What?

568
00:44:44,360 --> 00:44:46,720
Hey! I just saw Sis Waew

569
00:44:46,800 --> 00:44:48,240
-Sis Waew? Oh no!
-coming for the lottery money.

570
00:44:48,320 --> 00:44:50,360
Yeah, she's now
in the middle of the alley.

571
00:44:50,440 --> 00:44:53,160
-What? Sis Waew's here?
-Whoa, all nervous now!

572
00:44:53,240 --> 00:44:55,600
Can I borrow some money
to pay for the lottery?

573
00:44:55,680 --> 00:44:56,920
Wait.

574
00:44:57,000 --> 00:45:01,000
-Nammon, you bought it and didn't pay?
-I forgot.

575
00:45:01,080 --> 00:45:03,560
-What now?
-Oh my God!

576
00:45:03,640 --> 00:45:06,600
Both aunt and niece are terrible!

577
00:45:06,680 --> 00:45:08,040
-I can't take it!
-Whose side are you on?

578
00:45:08,680 --> 00:45:10,160
Oh no! I forgot.

579
00:45:10,240 --> 00:45:13,800
Sorry, I'm always on the winner's side.

580
00:45:13,880 --> 00:45:15,120
-I'm the winner!
-Oh, okay.

581
00:45:15,200 --> 00:45:17,760
-Hey. She's coming, right?
-Huh? She's here.

582
00:45:17,840 --> 00:45:18,840
-We have to hurry.
-Yeah.

583
00:45:18,920 --> 00:45:20,440
That Waew lady will go on and on!

584
00:45:20,520 --> 00:45:22,400
She'll be yelling
all the way to the market!

585
00:45:22,480 --> 00:45:24,520
-That's right.
-Wait!

586
00:45:24,600 --> 00:45:26,360
-Don't go left.
-Why?

587
00:45:26,440 --> 00:45:27,840
I saw the municipal truck parked there.

588
00:45:27,920 --> 00:45:29,840
Oh, perfect! I can grab some food.

589
00:45:29,920 --> 00:45:31,880
-Whoa! Are you crazy?
-Whoa!

590
00:45:31,960 --> 00:45:33,600
-People don't eat trash!
-What's with her?

591
00:45:33,680 --> 00:45:37,400
Bye! Can't get caught in this!
No money to pay, Sis Waew!

592
00:45:38,400 --> 00:45:39,640
These two don't have money!

593
00:45:39,720 --> 00:45:42,520
Miss Puna, don't pay attention to them.

594
00:45:42,600 --> 00:45:43,520
Let's go inside.

595
00:45:44,280 --> 00:45:45,320
Yes.

596
00:45:46,000 --> 00:45:46,960
After you.

597
00:45:47,560 --> 00:45:49,440
Enjoy the dessert!

598
00:46:02,960 --> 00:46:04,200
Hello.

599
00:46:07,120 --> 00:46:08,640
Got it. I'll head out.

600
00:46:51,000 --> 00:46:53,440
What's the matter, Wilai?
Why did you want to meet me?

601
00:46:53,520 --> 00:46:55,520
We could've just talked on the phone.

602
00:46:55,600 --> 00:46:57,520
Coming out like this
could be trouble if we're seen.

603
00:46:58,360 --> 00:47:01,560
Sorry. I'm just excited.

604
00:47:03,000 --> 00:47:04,240
Excited? About what?

605
00:47:05,440 --> 00:47:07,440
Puna just called.

606
00:47:07,520 --> 00:47:08,880
She got the evidence tape

607
00:47:08,960 --> 00:47:12,120
to use against Kitti and Singha.

608
00:47:13,360 --> 00:47:14,440
What?

609
00:47:15,440 --> 00:47:18,480
Puna got the tape from the teddy bear?

610
00:47:18,560 --> 00:47:19,440
Yes.

611
00:47:20,360 --> 00:47:23,320
It's time we get back at them.

612
00:47:24,360 --> 00:47:26,760
If we show the tape to the media,

613
00:47:27,320 --> 00:47:30,080
we can prove we were framed.

614
00:47:30,880 --> 00:47:33,960
But too bad, the case might be expired.

615
00:47:35,160 --> 00:47:36,200
Not yet.

616
00:47:37,080 --> 00:47:40,000
I had the lawyer check.

617
00:47:40,080 --> 00:47:41,960
There's still two weeks left.

618
00:47:42,560 --> 00:47:44,200
-Really?
-Yes.

619
00:47:44,280 --> 00:47:45,400
Will that be enough time?

620
00:47:46,120 --> 00:47:47,240
Yes.

621
00:47:47,320 --> 00:47:49,280
If we get it today, we'll make it.

622
00:47:50,680 --> 00:47:52,320
Finally, karma

623
00:47:52,400 --> 00:47:54,120
is catching up to them.

624
00:47:55,360 --> 00:47:57,320
We have to thank Puna.

625
00:47:57,400 --> 00:47:58,760
She made this possible.

626
00:47:59,480 --> 00:48:02,520
Yes, Puna really deserves the credit.

627
00:48:18,760 --> 00:48:20,120
Is it working, Mom?

628
00:48:20,200 --> 00:48:23,480
Oh, it's pretty bad, dear.

629
00:48:23,560 --> 00:48:24,640
Want a new phone?

630
00:48:25,960 --> 00:48:27,920
What about the data on this one?

631
00:48:28,600 --> 00:48:30,160
Give me a moment.

632
00:48:30,240 --> 00:48:32,520
If I can get it on,
I'll transfer the data for you.

633
00:48:32,600 --> 00:48:35,720
Alright? Just wait a sec, okay?

634
00:48:50,560 --> 00:48:54,400
-Mom. They're here!
-Huh?

635
00:48:55,240 --> 00:48:57,920
-Who, dear?
-The ones I told you about.

636
00:48:58,480 --> 00:48:59,520
Chit.

637
00:49:01,360 --> 00:49:02,320
Where are they?

638
00:49:02,920 --> 00:49:04,360
At the phone shop over there.

639
00:49:04,440 --> 00:49:06,200
Good. Lead the way.

640
00:49:06,280 --> 00:49:07,280
Yes.

641
00:49:14,120 --> 00:49:17,080
-Where's the tape?
-It's gone. I don't know where it went.

642
00:49:17,160 --> 00:49:18,160
NEXT EPISODE

643
00:49:18,240 --> 00:49:19,320
Have you noticed

644
00:49:20,200 --> 00:49:22,440
what this teacher's last name is?

645
00:49:22,520 --> 00:49:23,480
Damn it!

646
00:49:23,560 --> 00:49:25,880
Puna joined our company

647
00:49:26,560 --> 00:49:29,520
because she wants
the tape in this teddy bear!

648
00:49:29,600 --> 00:49:32,040
Most of the police are on their side.

649
00:49:32,120 --> 00:49:35,360
We might be the first ones they go after.

650
00:49:35,440 --> 00:49:36,760
I promise

651
00:49:36,840 --> 00:49:39,080
I'll get the tape back.

652
00:52:38,080 --> 00:52:40,840
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
